acAlarm.description: This MIB defines the enterprise-specific objects needed to support fault management of Audiocodes products. The MIB consists of: o Active alarm table o Alarm history table o Alarm notification varbinds

acActiveAlarmEntry.name: acActiveAlarmEntry
acActiveAlarmEntry.description: A conceptual row in the acActiveAlarmTable

acActiveAlarmSequenceNumber.name: acActiveAlarmSequenceNumber
acActiveAlarmSequenceNumber.description: The sequence number of the alarm raise trap.

acActiveAlarmSysuptime.name: acActiveAlarmSysuptime
acActiveAlarmSysuptime.description: The value of sysuptime at the time the alarm raise trap was sent

acActiveAlarmTrapOID.name: acActiveAlarmTrapOID
acActiveAlarmTrapOID.description: The OID of the notification trap

acActiveAlarmDateAndTime.name: acActiveAlarmDateAndTime
acActiveAlarmDateAndTime.description: The date and time at the time the alarm raise trap was sent.

acActiveAlarmName.name: acActiveAlarmName
acActiveAlarmName.description: The name of the alarm that was raised. This actually in the form of a number. Each kind of alarm has a unique number associated with it.

acActiveAlarmTextualDescription.name: acActiveAlarmTextualDescription
acActiveAlarmTextualDescription.description: Text that descries the alarm condition.

acActiveAlarmSource.name: acActiveAlarmSource
acActiveAlarmSource.description: The component in the system which raised the alarm.

acActiveAlarmEventType.name: acActiveAlarmEventType
acActiveAlarmEventType.description: The event type of the alarm.

acActiveAlarmProbableCause.name: acActiveAlarmProbableCause
acActiveAlarmProbableCause.description: The probable cause of the alarm.

acAlarmHistoryTable.name: acAlarmHistoryTable
acAlarmHistoryTable.description: A table of all raise-alarm and clear-alarm traps sent by the system. Internal to the system, this table of traps is a fixed size. Once the table reaches this size, older traps are removed to make room for new traps. The size of the table is the value of the nlmConfigLogEntryLimit (NOTIFICATION-LOG-MIB).

acAlarmHistoryEntry.description: A conceptual row in the acAlarmHistoryTable

acAlarmHistorySeverity.name: acAlarmHistorySeverity
acAlarmHistorySeverity.description: The severity of the alarm. A severity of warning, minor, major or critical indicates a raise trap. A severity of cleared indicates a clear trap.
